ANLSettings.StartText: Please select the measurement you want to perform
ANLSettings.MCLlowText: Now you will hear the story at a softer level. Signal me to decrease the volume until the story is too soft.
ANLSettings.MCLhighText: I will play a story for you. I want you to signal me to increase/decrease the story to determine your most comfortable listening level. I will instruct you along the way. First, signal me to increase the loudness of the speech until it is too loud.
ANLSettings.MCLtext: Ahora escuchará la historia a un nivel normal. Indíqueme que aumente o disminuya la historia a un nivel de escucha cómodo para ustedr. Imagine que soy el control de volumen de su televisor y que desea que el volumen esté ajustado de manera que puedes oír la televisión a un nivel cómodo durante toda la noche.
ANLSettings.BNLtext: You will listen to the same story with background noise of several people talking at the same time. First signal me to turn up the noise level until the noise is too loud. Then you will signal me to turn down the noise level until the story becomes very clear. Finally signal me to turn up the noise until we reach the MAXIMUM level that you would be willing to 'put up with' for a long time while following the story.
